MyCanopy L1 is a Python-based Layer 1 blockchain deployed on the Canopy Network testnet, designed to demonstrate a fully functional on-chain execution environment.
Consensus: The chain uses a proof-of-work mechanism with adjustable difficulty. Each block contains a SHA-256 hash of the previous block, a Unix timestamp, a list of transactions, and a log of smart contract calls — ensuring full immutability and auditability of all on-chain activity.
Smart Contract Engine: Contracts are deployed via a ContractRegistry and assigned a unique deterministic address (0x + SHA-256 digest). Each contract holds isolated on-chain state and exposes callable methods. Execution errors are caught and surfaced without corrupting chain state.
Token Standard: MyCanopy L1 includes a native ERC20-like token contract supporting mint, transfer, and balanceOf operations. Total supply is enforced at the contract level, and only the contract owner can mint new tokens.
Governance: An on-chain voting contract allows participants to create proposals and cast yes/no votes. Each address may vote once per proposal, and results are tallied and stored immutably on-chain.
Architecture: The codebase is split into two modules — chain.py for core blockchain logic and contracts.py for the contract engine. No external dependencies are required beyond Python 3.10+. Future development will introduce a REST API layer, wallet management with asymmetric key pairs, and peer-to-peer node communication.
